361
00:24:29,917 --> 00:24:32,560
But it's going to be traditional animation. No worries.

362
00:24:33,001 --> 00:24:34,002
Awesome. Thanks.

363
00:24:36,769 --> 00:24:38,610
Hi, thank you for the presentation.

364
00:24:38,630 --> 00:24:40,231
Amazing art all the way.

365
00:24:40,451 --> 00:24:43,512
So my question is for the large object that you were

366
00:24:43,552 --> 00:24:48,154
describing on the background that had a 3D effect, was that

367
00:24:48,394 --> 00:24:51,535
a normal map thingy, or is that like 3D model?

368
00:24:52,444 --> 00:24:56,428
No, it's actually just a simple cylinder

369
00:24:56,448 --> 00:25:01,432
that Omar added the option.

370
00:25:01,652 --> 00:25:04,434
When I wanted a sprite to behave like a 3D object,

371
00:25:04,815 --> 00:25:08,398
it's just behaving like a cylinder based on the camera.

372
00:25:09,078 --> 00:25:11,820
So there's no normal map, no modeling.

373
00:25:12,541 --> 00:25:14,863
If you look closely, it's not very...

374
00:25:15,704 --> 00:25:16,664
very well made.

375
00:25:18,264 --> 00:25:19,645
But it does a trick.

376
00:25:19,845 --> 00:25:22,245
And if you look at the pillars, it works better

377
00:25:22,285 --> 00:25:23,726
because it's very cylinder.

378
00:25:23,746 --> 00:25:25,486
OK, awesome.

379
00:25:25,506 --> 00:25:25,826
Thank you.

380
00:25:26,147 --> 00:25:26,567
